"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416433","Department for Education","false","2015-09-09","<p>The Secretary of State purchased, in the name of the Edge Academy Trust, 946 Bristol Road Northfield Birmingham B31 2LQ for the sum of £1,650,000 (exclusive of VAT).</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2015-09-09T10:14:19.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416433/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416433/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416433/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-09-04","Education Funding Agency: Birmingham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much the Education Funding Authority paid for the Maddox offices site located in Birmingham Northfield.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","9062"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416434","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-14","<p>The Government carried out an analysis of the impact of the National Living Wage, using a similar approach to that published by the Office for Budget Responsibility, which considered the implications at the business, sector, regional and aggregate economy level.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will publish a full impact assessment for the introduction of the National Living Wage alongside the implementing regulations. These regulations will be debated in both Houses of Parliament in time to come into force on 1 April 2016.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","8843","2015-09-14T16:01:54.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416434/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416434/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416434/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-04","Care Homes: Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent discussions he has had with the Welsh Assembly Government on the level of care home fees and planned changes to the national minimum wage.","false","Biography information for Mr Mark Williams","Ceredigion","Mr Mark Williams","8848"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416435","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-14","<p>The Government carried out an analysis of the impact of the National Living Wage, using a similar approach to that published by the Office for Budget Responsibility, which considered the implications at the business, sector, regional and aggregate economy level.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will publish a full impact assessment for the introduction of the National Living Wage alongside the implementing regulations. These regulations will be debated in both Houses of Parliament in time to come into force on 1 April 2016.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","8848","2015-09-14T16:01:54.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416435/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416435/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416435/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-04","Minimum Wage: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the effect of changes to the minimum wage on the care sector in Wales.","false","Biography information for Mr Mark Williams","Ceredigion","Mr Mark Williams","8843"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416436","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-14","<p>As the Secretary of State made clear in his speech on 17 July, we want to make sure that we have a modern and effective prison estate that supports rehabilitative outcomes for offenders held in custody. We will set out our plans in due course.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-09-14T14:48:36.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416436/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416436/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416436/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-04","Prisons: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps he is taking to modernise the prison estate; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Maria Caulfield","Lewes","Maria Caulfield","8656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416437","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-11","<p>In his Budget of 8 July the Chancellor of the Exchequer announced the Government’s intention to put Transport for the North (TfN) on a statutory footing with statutory duties.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government is working with TfN on an appropriate statutory framework and intends to announce its plans in due course.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-09-11T11:50:15.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416437/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416437/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416437/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-04","Transport for the North","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to Paragraph 1.301 of the Summer Budget 2015, what legislation he plans to bring forward to establish Transport for the North as a statutory body; and what statutory duties he intends Transport for the North to have.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8546"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416438","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-14","<p>The National Planning Policy Framework and planning guidance expect local authorities to meet the development needs of their area. Under the terms of the Greater Manchester Agreement, the directly elected Mayor will have powers to produce a statutory spatial framework covering all 10 unitary authorities. This framework will need to be consistent with the National Planning Policy Framework.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-09-14T14:06:11.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416438/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416438/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416438/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-04","Regional Planning and Development: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to the Summer Budget 2015, Paragraph 1.284, whether the new planning powers of the Greater Manchester city region will include the ability to depart from the National Planning Policy Framework.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416439","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-14","<p>In the July Budget the Government announced that a Greater Manchester Land Commission would be created to oversee the efficient utilisation of the public sector estate in Manchester. It will create a comprehensive database of all public sector land, identifying barriers to its disposal, and developing solutions to address those barriers to help Greater Manchester meet its goal to deliver more than 10,000 new homes per annum. The Land Commission will be jointly chaired by the Mayor and Housing Minister, and will include Ministers from key land-owning Departments. We will work to create the Commission in collaboration with the Greater Manchester Combined Authority.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-09-14T13:55:45.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416439/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416439/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416439/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-04","Greater Manchester Land Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the powers and responsibilities of the Greater Manchester Land Commission will be; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8588"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416440","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-11","<p>Transport for the North (TfN) is currently working in partnership with Network Rail in order to advise the Government on the strategic investment priorities for the North of England.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We are currently exploring options to establish TfN as a statutory body with statutory duties so that it can further drive economic growth in the North. As we take forward these discussions with TfN, Network Rail and others we will consider the working relationships between the various parties.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-09-11T11:59:20.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416440/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416440/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-04","Transport for the North","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what responsibilities of Network Rail will be transferred to Transport for the North.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8589"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416441","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-11","<p>As Transport for the North (TFN) is working in partnership with the Department for Transport, they have asked the Secretary of State to approve the appointment which they will make. The Secretary of State is subject to Parliamentary scrutiny.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-09-11T12:03:17.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416441/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416441/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-04","Transport for the North","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the appointment of the Chair of Transport for the North will be subject to parliamentary scrutiny.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416442","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-14","<p>The National Planning Policy Framework, informed by Planning Guidance, sets out the policy principles relating to viability assessment. However, the Government does not believe that imposition of a single viability model would be appropriate, which gives local authorities the freedom to set their own approach to assessing viability of new developments.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-09-14T13:54:12.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416442/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416442/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-04","Regional Planning and Development: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to the Summer Budget 2015, Paragraph 1.284, whether the Greater Manchester city region will be able to set its own guidance on viability of new developments.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8542"
