er Department's (a) total expenditure and (b) expenditure on governance, democracy and human rights projects has been in each country in Africa in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Richard Fuller","Bedford","Richard Fuller","8535"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416822","Home Office","false","2015-09-10","<p>The revised guidance will be published shortly.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-09-10T13:51:36.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416822/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416822/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416822/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-09-04","Asylum: Pregnancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the Answer of 24 February 2014, to Question 187811, when she plans to publish the revised guidance relating to procedures for dispersing and accommodating pregnant women who seek asylum in the UK.","false","Biography information for Richard Fuller","Bedford","Richard Fuller","8690"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416823","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-14","<p>This information is not held centrally.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2015-09-14T13:29:03.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416823/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416823/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416823/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-04","Prisoners: Pregnancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many pregnant women have begun a prison sentence in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Richard Fuller","Bedford","Richard Fuller","8861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416824","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-14","<p>Our productivity plan <em>Fixing the Foundations </em>identified the importance of collaboration between universities and industry and set a goal to increase the income they earn from working with business and others to £5 billion per annum by 2025.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Dowling Review, to which we will respond around the time of the Spending Review, stressed the need to make it easier for business to find help and support from universities and Government.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>R&amp;D Tax Credits remain the largest source of Government support for business investment in R&amp;D and make an important contribution to innovation in SMEs.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-09-14T16:59:10.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416824/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416824/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416824/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-04","Science: Business","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what plans the Government has to support the development of (a) university spin-out businesses in the field of science and (b) small businesses in the field of science.","false","Biography information for Dr James Davies","Vale of Clwyd","Dr James Davies","9036"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416825","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-14","<p>The Government has named 285 employers to date, and there have been 16 successful appeals. HMRC has issued 791 Notices of Underpayment (NoU) since 1 October 2013.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The criteria on which appeals against naming are considered are that it would not be in the public interest, it would be a national security issue, or that the employer or their family would suffer personal harm.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Not all employers who are issued an NoU since 1 October 2013 will be named. Employers must have owed arrears of over £100. The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) also only names employers who have paid back all of the arrears owed – if, following the issue of an NoU, the employer has yet to complete a schedule of payment of arrears to their workers, has challenged the NoU, or is being taken to court to recover arrears that remain unpaid, their details will not be passed to BIS for naming.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-09-14T14:57:49.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416825/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416825/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416825/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-04","Minimum Wage: Underpayments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many employers have been issued with a Notice of Underpayment of the national minimum wage by HM Revenue and Customs in cases where the investigation began on or after 1 October 2013; how many of those employers have successfully appealed against being named and shamed; and how many such employers have been named and shamed to date.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","8860"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416826","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-14","<p>The National Minimum Wage campaign launched on 29 July 2015. Information on the number of employers, workers covered and total arrears identified through the campaign will be made available when details for each voluntary disclosure have been finalised.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-09-14T14:45:25.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416826/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416826/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416826/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-04","Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many employers have taken advantage of the national minimum wage campaign announced on 30 July to self-report their non-compliance with the national minimum wage; how many workers have been identified as having been underpaid by these employers; and what the total sum is of underpayments involved.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","8859"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416827","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-14","<p>The Government’s budget for HMRC’s enforcement of the National Minimum Wage has been:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>(a) 2013-14 – £8.3m</p><p> </p><p>(b) 2014-15 – £9.2m</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The budget for 2015-16 was raised to £12.2m, and following an additional £1m announced in the Summer Budget, is now £13.2m.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-09-14T14:47:00.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416827/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416827/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416827/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-04","Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the level of expenditure was on enforcement of the national minimum wage by HM Revenue and Customs in (a) 2013-14 and (b) 2014-15; and what the final budget is for such expenditure in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","8858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416828","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-09","<p>The Hitachi Train manufacturing facility at Newton Aycliffe was officially opened by the Prime Minister on 3rd September 2015. The facility has already employed over 100 staff, increasing to 400 by Easter 2016.　 The facility is ramping up for a November 2015 start and will go into full production next year on IEP trains.　 Production of the Abellio ScotRail trains will also commence at the facility in line with plans to enter service from late 2017.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-09-09T16:22:51.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416828/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416828/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416828/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-04","Hitachi: Newton Aycliffe","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when the new Hitachi Trains factory at Newton Aycliffe will be (a) officially opened and (b) working at full capacity.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","8716"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416829","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-09","<p>The first IEP trains will be manufactured by Hitachi at their Kasado factory in Japan until production at Newton Aycliffe commences in autumn 2016. The remaining trains will be assembled at the Newton Aycliffe site.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-09-09T15:15:42.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416829/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416829/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416829/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-04","First Great Western: Rolling Stock","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, where the new Inter City Express train sets for First Great Western will be (a) manufactured and (b) assembled.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","8717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416830","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-09","<p>The first IEPs will be delivered as planned from May 2017.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-09-09T14:21:33.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416830/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416830/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416830/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-04","First Great Western: Rolling Stock","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the timetable for the delivery of the first train for First Great Western of 25 May 2017 will be met.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","8718"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416831","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-09","<p>Parts for the Virgin Trains East Coast line standard class buffet facilities will be manufactured in Germany and then installed at Newton Aycliffe. 72% of the parts, systems and operations sourced by Hitachi Rail Europe for the IEP have been purchased from UK-based businesses.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-09-09T15:12:17.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416831/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416831/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416831/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-04","East Coast Railway Line: Rolling Stock","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, where the modification to include a buffet car in standard class of the IEP train sets for the East Coast line will be (a) manufactured and (b) assembled.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","8719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416832","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-09","<p>The inclusion of a standard class buffet facilities will be accommodated within the existing delivery schedule. Trains will enter passenger service on the East Coast Main Line as planned from 2018.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-09-09T15:21:12.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416832/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416832/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416832/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-04","East Coast Railway Line: Rolling Stock","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment has been made of the effect to the delivery timetable for IEP trains for the East Coast line of the modifications to include a buffet car in standard class.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","8720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416833","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-11","<p>The IEP trains for Virgin East Coast Trains will be delivered with standard class buffet facilities within the existing delivery schedule. Trains will enter passenger service as planned from 2018.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-09-11T13:35:23.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416833/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416833/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416833/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-04","East Coast Railway Line: Rolling Stock","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of the time taken for Hitachi to modify IEP trains for East Coast to include a buffet car in standard class.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","8889"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416834","Speaker's Committee for the Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority","false","2015-11-23","<p>IPSA's Corporate Plan identifies Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) and associated targets, each of which is the responsibility of a senior manager. Performance against KPIs is measured and reported monthly to IPSA’s Senior Management Team (SMT) and the Board and published on IPSA's website. Operational performance targets for the financial year are contained within IPSA's Annual Report and Accounts, which are also published on IPSA's website.</p><p>Further information on IPSA’s performance can be found in the Corporate Plan, available on IPSA’s website.</p><p>Staff capacity, performance and welfare, as well as comprehensive financial management information, are measured and reported monthly to IPSA’s SMT and the Board as part of our KPIs. From this IPSA is able to identify any issues regarding productivity, efficiency or cost and address them accordingly.</p><p>All IPSA employees have performance objectives, which are aligned with IPSA’s Corporate Plan. Employees are managed against their objectives, including through formal quarterly reviews to ensure performance and productivity are satisfactory.<strong></strong></p><p>A staff engagement survey is also undertaken each year, which identifies any issues of concern which may affect staff productivity.</p><p>To ensure IPSA continues to increase both efficiency and productivity it measures performance against our Key Performance Indicators (KPIs). This activity enables IPSA to identify any issues and put relevant plans in place to ensure that productivity continues to improve.</p>","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","8401 ; 8701","2015-11-23T17:19:47.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416834/answer","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416834/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416834/answer",,,,,"90","Speaker's Committee for the Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority","Speaker's Committee for the Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority","2015-09-04","Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for Broxbourne, representing the Speaker's Committee for the Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority, how IPSA measures levels of productivity of its staff.","false","Biography information for Philip Boswell","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Phil Boswell","8700"
